The paper proposes a new strategy for measuring relatedness between tasks in multitask learning, which is a common topic in machine learning. The paper focuses on joint learning of shared parameters and shared feature representations, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
